    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/5126</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2745. Your 2664, September 18 [<hi rend="italic">2602, October 15</hi>]<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d111fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_974">p. 974</ref>.</note> Act
                    of Congress approved October 6 makes it unlawful for any person in the United
                    States, except with license granted by authority of the President “to trade or
                    attempt to trade either directly or indirectly, with, to or from, or for, or on
                    account of, or on behalf of, or for the benefit of, any other person, with
                    knowledge or reasonable cause to believe that such other person is an enemy or
                    ally of enemy, or is conducting or taking part in such trade, directly or
                    indirectly, for, or on account of, or on behalf of, or for the benefit of, an
                    enemy or ally of enemy.” By proclamation of October 12,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d111fn2">Executive order of Oct. 12, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_963">p. 963</ref>.</note> President gives to War Trade
                    Board authority to administer this provision of law. Grubnau &amp; Son state
                    senior member of company has lived forty-four years in the United States and has
                    been American citizen thirty-four years, and that other members of concern are
                    all native Americans.</p>
                <p>Bring these facts to attention French Government and suggest that in view thereof
                    restrictive measures referred to seem unnecessary and perhaps derogatory to
                    commercial interests of both countries. Copies of law and proclamation being
                    mailed you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
